This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically clinical concept extraction, and explores the use of advanced embedding methods and representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates and compares different embedding methods, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pre-trained language models like ELMo and BERT, which are popular in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) tasks, as it evaluates the performance of different embedding methods on four concept extraction corpora. Finally, the paper discusses the semantic information encoded by contextual embeddings, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
